_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                 1BBB 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details         
;PREVIOUS CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC STUDIES HAVE SHOWN THAT WILD-TYPE
HUMAN HEMOGLOBIN CAN ADOPT TWO STABLE QUATERNARY
STRUCTURES, ONE FOR DEOXYHEMOGLOBIN (THE T STATE, E.G.
PROTEIN DATA BANK ENTRIES 2HHB AND 1HHB) AND ONE FOR
LIGANDED HEMOGLOBIN (THE R STATE, E.G. ENTRY 1HHO).  THIS
STRUCTURE OF HUMAN CARBONMONOXYHEMOGLOBIN REPRESENTS A
SECOND QUATERNARY STRUCTURE (TERMED THE R2-STATE) FOR
LIGANDED HUMAN HEMOGLOBIN.  IT IS SIMILAR, BUT NOT
IDENTICAL, TO THE LIGANDED STRUCTURE OF A NATURALLY
OCCURRING MUTANT HEMOGLOBIN, HEMOGLOBIN YPSILANTI (ENTRY
1CMY).
;
